          "reviewBody": "I visited Rajagiri Public School Kalamassery for the admission of my grandchild recently. The school authorities welcomed me with a warm smile and explained about the admission formalities. I felt that this school will be the best institution for the overall development of my grandchild, I am sure that my grandchild will be very comfortable here and this school will become his second home.\nIn this esteemed institution, all facilities are there, well equipped classrooms, the most competent teachers, efficient administrative staff, and over and above all an excellent setup for good quality education. Big campus area for children for proper study and the facilities for extra curricular activities are available. A well established school with very good infrastructure.The present director of the school is the gem of a priest with full of broadminded ideas for the future development of this esteemed institution.\nPraveen Ranjit\nRetired professor\nSt. Albert's college,\nErnakulam",
